### ü§ñ AI Competency Framework for Teachers: Empowering Educators

<div style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #ffeacc, #fff5eb);
            padding: 2em;
            border-radius: 20px;
            color: #4b2e2e;
            font-weight: bold;
            box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);">

* **Bridging the Gap:** This framework defines the **AI knowledge, skills, and values** educators need to **thrive in AI-enriched learning environments**.
* **Ethical Grounding:** Built on principles of **human-centred values**, **teacher agency**, and **sustainability**.
* **Five Core Dimensions:**

  * üß† **Human-Centred Mindset** ‚Äì Upholding dignity, agency, and human oversight in the classroom.
  * ‚öñÔ∏è **Ethics of AI** ‚Äì Navigating bias, transparency, and responsibility.
  * üíª **AI Foundations & Applications** ‚Äì Understanding basic AI tools and their use cases in education.
  * üë©‚Äçüè´ **AI Pedagogy** ‚Äì Designing **learner-centred** AI-enhanced teaching and assessment.
  * üìö **AI for Professional Learning** ‚Äì Using AI for continuous personal and professional development.
* **Three Proficiency Levels:**

  * üéì **Acquire** ‚Äì Build awareness and basic AI literacy.
  * üöÄ **Deepen** ‚Äì Apply AI meaningfully in teaching contexts.
  * üåü **Create** ‚Äì Innovate with AI and lead responsible integration in institutions.

</div>

[read more](https://https://www.unesco.org/en/articles/ai-competency-framework-teachers)

