### üéì AI Competency Framework for Students: Learning to Shape the Future

<div style="background: linear-gradient(to right, #e0f7ec, #f0fff8);
            padding: 2em;
            border-radius: 20px;
            color: #1b3f36;
            font-weight: bold;
            box-shadow: 0 0 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);">

* **AI as a Life Skill:** As AI becomes part of everyday life, students must be equipped to engage with it **safely, critically, and creatively**.
* **Curricular Imperative:** Schools worldwide must embed **AI learning goals** to develop **responsible digital citizens and future innovators**.
* **Four Key Competency Dimensions:**

  * ü§ù **Human-Centred Mindset** ‚Äì Emphasizing empathy, inclusion, and social responsibility in AI use.
  * ‚öñÔ∏è **Ethics of AI** ‚Äì Cultivating **judgment and accountability** in dealing with bias, privacy, and fairness.
  * ‚öôÔ∏è **AI Techniques & Applications** ‚Äì Building **foundational knowledge** of how AI works and where it‚Äôs used.
  * üõ†Ô∏è **AI System Design** ‚Äì Encouraging students to **create inclusive and sustainable AI solutions**.
* **Three Development Levels:**

  * üß† **Understand** ‚Äì Grasp AI basics and ethical implications.
  * üõ†Ô∏è **Apply** ‚Äì Use AI tools to solve real-world problems.
  * üåü **Create** ‚Äì Innovate with AI and design systems responsibly.
* **Vision for AI Learners:** Students are seen as **AI co-creators**, not just users ‚Äî capable of **lifelong learning**, **critical thinking**, and **ethical innovation**.

</div>

[read more](https://www.unesco.org/en/articles/ai-competency-framework-students)

